VERDICT (honest):
  - The autonomous-recall PLUMBING is COMPLETE and CORRECT end-to-end:
    /v1/chat auto_recall:true -> prefill query -> read resident-cache GLOBAL-layer K
    (new additive engine verb gemma4_kv_read_global_k) -> compute the 256-bit C2 LSH
    signature in-daemon (recall.rs, byte-exact port of discrete_resolve.py;
    cross-checked 256/256 against the Python registry build) -> Hamming-match the
    episode registry -> auto-gemma4_kv_replay the best episode if it clears TAU_BITS.
  - The REPLAY-CONDITIONING mechanism works (B6 reproduced this run): explicit replay
    of ep_wiki makes the 12B answer the verbatim ground truth incl. the @-@ telltale;
    no-recall hallucinates. (transcripts below)
  - The recall SELECTION does NOT work: the C2 mean-of-global-K signature is NOT
    discriminative enough to map a short QUESTION to its answer-PASSAGE. Measured
    below. So G-CHAT-B3-RECALL is RED on leg (a) right-episode recall. Leg (b)
    foreign-reject "passes" only trivially (nothing ever clears TAU, so nothing
    spuriously fires) — which is the same coin as leg (a) failing.
  - This is reported as an HONEST NEGATIVE with the crux precisely located (below),
    NOT faked. auto_recall defaults OFF = byte-untouched null floor; no closed gate
    regresses.

