--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 THE EXTRACTION GAP WE FOUND AND FIXED (representation parity) — receipts
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  First registry was built from the on-disk ep.k owner-K dumps.  Comparing a query
  sig against it scored ~124-140/256 (below the random 128 floor for the foreign).
  Even feeding an episode's OWN passage text back as the query scored ~132 (random) —
  a self-match should be ~256.  Root cause, measured by dumping the live read_global_k
  buffer and diffing against ep.k for the SAME tokens/positions/layers (homarus, 179 pos):
      live_cache_K norm / ep.k norm = 0.500  EXACTLY  (std 0.000 across all positions)
      per-position cosine(live, ep.k) = ~0.00  (uncorrelated direction)
      relL2(live, ep.k) = ~1.12 on every global layer L in {5,11,17,23,29,35,41,47}
  ==> the one-shot gemma4_decode_cuda path that CAPTURED the episodes and the resident
      g4_kv_step prefill the daemon decodes through produce DIFFERENT global-K for the
      same input (exact 0.5x magnitude + decorrelated direction).  The query can only
      read the resident-cache representation, so the on-disk-ep.k registry is not
      comparable to it.
  FIX: rebuild the registry from the SAME path the query uses (gemma4_kv_read_global_k
      over the resident cache of each episode's own tokens).  This is parity-correct and
      raised all scores to ~155-182 — but see the residual negative below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 LEG (a) RIGHT-EPISODE RECALL — query-vs-PARITY-registry agreement matrix (AS MEASURED)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  TAU_BITS=168.  argmax = highest-agreement episode.  want = the topically-correct one.

   query                                         wiki homarus headlam  argmax    want      hit?
   "Who is Robert Boulter?"                       160   160   162    ep_headlam  ep_wiki    NO
   "What is Homarus gammarus?"                     169   159   153    ep_wiki     ep_homarus NO
   "Who was Frank Headlam?"                        164   162   162    ep_wiki     ep_headlam NO
   "Tell me about the European lobster."           162   166   158    ep_homarus  ep_homarus YES
   "Who was the Australian air force cmdr Headlam?"182   172   178    ep_wiki     ep_headlam NO
   "What is the capital of France?" (foreign)      158   160   154    ep_homarus  (reject)   --
   "How do I bake sourdough bread?"  (foreign)     166   174   174    ep_hom/head (reject)   --

  - The right episode is the argmax in only 1/5 topical queries.
  - Scores cluster at ~155-182 with NO relevance ordering: the foreign "sourdough"
    query (174) outscores most on-topic queries.  The signature does not separate
    relevant from irrelevant.
  - At TAU=168, the daemon never fires on the topical queries (the relevant episode's
    score sits at/below 168) yet a foreign query (sourdough=174) WOULD fire on a
    wrong episode — so no TAU choice both fires-on-target and rejects-foreign.

