 CONTROL — the replay mechanism itself works (B6 reproduced this run)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 A) auto_recall:false (null floor, NO recall) — "Who is Robert Boulter?":
    "Robert Boulter is a British actor and comedian. He is best known for his work in
     the British television series "The Thick of It" and "Veep". He has also appeared
     in films such as "The King's Speech" and "The Iron Lady"..."          <-- HALLUCINATION

 B) EXPLICIT replay ep_wiki npos=84 — "...who is Robert Boulter and what role on The Bill?":
    "Robert Boulter is an English film , television and theatre actor . He had a guest
     @-@ starring role on the television series The Bill in 2000 . This was followed by
     a starring role in the play Herons written by Simon Stephens , which was performed
     in 2001 at the Royal Court Theatre ..."                               <-- VERBATIM GROUND TRUTH (@-@ telltale)

  ==> conditioning works; if the C2 sig SELECTED ep_wiki, auto-recall would emit (B).
      The whole gap is the SELECTION representation, not the replay or the plumbing.

